  "narrative_arc": "Woman enslaved as a reproductive vessel in a theocratic state. Atwood documents the architecture of total control — the uniform, the restricted walking routes, the forbidden reading, the mandated rape ceremony, and the small resistances (butter on skin, whispered words).",
